  "doc_id": "14282",
  "text": "If we extend the flag F • to a complete flag in Ker(u), then the stabilizer of the extended flag is a Borel subgroup B ⊂ Q. The orbit O ρ is a union of certain Borbits in Gr, that is Schubert cells. So the cardinality of O ρ is a sum of powers of q given by the well known formula for the dimension of the Schubert cells (see e.g. Appendix to Chapter II of [CITATION_1] ). We will denote this cardinality by P ρ . Note that the Jordan type of u| D/W for W ∈ O ρ is ν ′ := ρ(ν) where ρ(ν) is defined as the partition dual toν",
